        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 16 at 6:37PM EDT by NWS Cleveland OH</headline>
        <description>At 637 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Harmonsburg, or 9 miles west of Meadville, moving northeast at 40
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Edinboro, Cambridge Springs, Waterford, Harmonsburg, Saegertown,
Conneautville, Mill Village, Venango, and Woodcock.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
